  "text": "CEL files from sorted cell type samples from IRIS (GSE22886 [CITATION_1] ) and the Human body index (GSE7307) were normalized separately using frma [CITATION_2] . In GSE7307, we extracted the profiles from all immune cells (32 profiles from monocyte, T cell and B cell lineages) and colon tissues (2 profiles). We created a combined cell type gene expression matrix, corrected for dataset of origin effects using Combat [CITATION_3] , and subsequently averaged probesets into genes. This resulted in the creation of an expression matrix of 130 expression profiles (Supplementary Table S2 ), which we then standardized using zscores and averaged into major cell lineages split into resting and activation/memory state.",
